      "span_text": "These results are also in good agreement with the observations of Fiser et al. [CITATION_1] which showed that monkeys fed a high-fat, high-cholesterol diet had impaired development of precipitating antibodies to ovalbumin-enhanced susceptibility to tuberculin antigen and an increased rate of clearance of colloidal carbon from blood."
